import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['speed'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['speed'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['speed'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of speed?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['dir'], data['speed'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Direction')
    ax.set_ylabel('Speed')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between direction and speed?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    dirCat_count = data['dirCat'].value_counts()
    dirCat_count.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of direction categories?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=2, figsize=(10, 10))
    categories = data['dirCat'].unique()
    colors = ['blue', 'green', 'red', 'orange', 'purple', 'brown', 'pink', 'gray']
    for i, category in enumerate(categories):
        ax = axs[i//2, i%2]
        category_data = data[data['dirCat'] == category]
        ax.scatter(category_data['direction'], category_data['speed'], color=colors[i])
        ax.set_xlabel('Direction')
        ax.set_ylabel('Speed')
        ax.set_title(f'{category} Direction Category')
    fig.suptitle('What is the distribution of direction and speed for each direction category?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
